summary: I am a graduate student researcher studying organism development by looking at totipotent cell differentiation through to cell fate commitment in tomato plants. I am also an avid knitter, gardener, baker and dinosaur impersonator. My time as an improv actress makes me an entertaining public speaker and science song writer which feeds in to my love of science through teaching and SciComm.Check out my SciComm blog at BasicallyScience.org or find me on twitter @CatsCauseTypos
